&lt;p&gt;Registered Nursing Associate- Band 4 (4 posts)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forward Thinking Birmingham - Community Mental Health Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following significant new investment we are expanding our community mental health teams.  This has provided us with the exciting opportunity to recruit Registered Nursing Associates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be supported by a multidisciplinary team and will be under the leadership of registered nurses.  You will be provided with the opportunity to broaden your skill set and gain valuable mental health experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The workload is fast paced and therefore you will be required to manage your own time to meet the needs of your case load and the team.  You will have a particular focus on the physical health needs of our service users.  This is a community post so you will need to meet the travel requirements.  The teams operate Monday to Friday 9am-5pm. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are posts within each of our hubs across the City in Selly Oak, Sutton Coldfield, Lozells and Yardley.  We promote agile working therefore your time will be spent between working in the hub, at community settings including service users’ homes and working from home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Birmingham is an exciting, vibrant City to live and work.  It has one of the most diverse populations in the Country. We are a mental health service that celebrates this diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all service users and employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits of working with FTB (employed by BWC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days holiday, plus bank holidays increasing to 33 days holiday with continuous service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childcare Vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent opportunities for career development as we continue to develop new transformational services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert clinical supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Further Information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah-Jayne Alleyne, Clinical Nurse Educator, Mobile: 07387 010920, Secure email: sarah-jayne.alleyne@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Smith, Clinical Nurse Educator Mental Health Services – Inpatient Lead, Ext. 6938 | 0121 333 9955&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 6 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
